name: Jack-o_Challenge_Shurik
description:
*****DISCLAIMER*****

I can only get consistent results in models like realisticVisionV12_v12 by using ControlNet. I believe the issue is that the real photo models think the butts are breasts 80-90% of the time. It also doesn't know how to properly proportion the legs with the torso. But it does sort of work. If you roll the dice enough, you might be able to get a good result without ControlNet. I used Guidance Strength of 0.6

I hate uploading multiple versions, but I think I have to.

V20 is a little better at realistic and is severely over trained for anime. Might need ControlNet 🤷‍♂️

V19 is decent at anime

V16 is decent at realism without ControlNet

V13 makes fun images that I like.

V9 is decent at realism without ControlNet (maybe the most consistent)

Swap out different models and see which works best for you.

I know 3 other people have uploaded this similar pose. I've not tested any of them. I'm sure each has it's advantages and disadvantages.

  • https://civitai.com/models/10296/jack-o-pose-concept-lora

  • https://civitai.com/models/10825/jack-o-pose

  • https://civitai.com/models/10353/jack-o-challenge-pose-lora-1-mb

This model really broke my spirits. I think I need a week to recover.
